In LATEX, drawing a chessboard using the FEN notation is a simple task. We can use the `\board` command to draw the chessboard and the `\startFEN` command to declare the FEN notation. For example, we can use the following code to create LATEX code containing all the necessary commands and packages:

```latex
% !TeX program = lualatex
% !TeX encoding = utf8
\documentclass[11pt]{article}
\usepackage{chess}
\begin{document}
\board[setup=starting,fen=rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1]
\end{document}
```

This code will generate a PDF document displaying the FEN notation of the chessboard. The `\board` command in this code defines the size and layout of the chessboard, specifying the position of each piece. It also specifies the color and size of the pieces. The `\startFEN` command declares the FEN notation, which includes all the positions and pieces on the chessboard. The `\board` and `\startFEN` commands can be used to draw multiple different chessboard states.

